description.p:
The process of the present invention comprises:
i)a step for digesting DNA into several fragments which have single-strand cohesive ends by using restriction enzyme, and separately from the above, for preparing hairpin loop adaptors which have the single-strand cohesive end which can be complementarily combined and ligated on the both ends of the DNA fragment obtained in the above;
ii) a step for ligating the DNA fragments with the hairpin loop adapters prepared in step i) by using DNA ligase;
iii)a step for removing DNA fragments and hairpin loop adapters which have not participated in the ligation reaction by using exonuclease;
iv) optionally, a step for eliminating the hairpin loop by using alkaline solution, RNase or single strand specific exonuclease; and
v) a step for amplifying the DNA fragment by using DNA polymerase and primer which can combine complementarily on the residual sequence from the adapters to obtain DNA in large amount through Polymerase Chain Reaction from DNA of which sequence is completely unknown.

In addition, another object of the present invention may be achieved by providing a process for making library of DNA fragment of which terminal sequence are known by using DNA of which base sequence is completely unknown, which comprises:
i)a step for digesting DNA into fragments which have single-strand cohesive end by using restriction enzyme, and separately from the above, for preparing a series of hairpin loop adapters which have single-strand cohesive end of which base sequence is known;
ii)a step for ligating the DNA fragments with the hairpin loop adapters prepared in the above step i) by using DNA ligase;
iii) a step for eliminating the hairpin loop only from the DNA fragments which contain hairpin loop adapter, obtained in step ii) by treating alkaline solution, RNase of single strand specific exonuclease.
